Black can go for ...g7-g5.} ({Also in this position, Black can play} 6... Bg6 {
[%cal Gg8h6,Gh6f5,Gg8e7,Ge7f5] with the idea to free the f5-square for the
knight.} 7. Nbd2 Nh6 8. Nb3 Nf5 9. Bd2 Be7 10. g4 $1 {A typical idea in such
positions! White drives the knight from the active position and begins to gain
space on the kingside.} Nh4 ({After} 10... Nh6 {White can opt for} 11. Ne1 $1 {
Typical manoeuvre in this pawn structure. The knight is heading for g2.
Afterwards, White can start advancing his kingside pawns.} O-O ({The attempt
