13. Rc7 $16 {we have a position which is similar to the main line.}) (9...
Qxc3+ 10. Bd2 Qxc2 11. Qxb7 $18) 10. dxc5 a6 ({The move} 10... Qxc3+ {loses on
the spot after} 11. Bd2 Qxc5 12. Qxb7 $18) 11. O-O Qc7 {Black has a better
pawn structure but White's advantage in the development is a way more
important.} 12. Nd4 Bg6 13. Qb4 Nd7 14. Na4 Ne7 15. Nb6 Nxb6 16. cxb6 Qd7 17.
Qb2 Rc8 18. Rfd1 $16 {[%cal Gc2c4] White's advantage is obvious. He is ready
to follow with c2-c4. Huschenbet-Onischuk 2017 1-0} (18. Rac1 $1 $16)) (8...
Qxc3+ $2 9. Bd2 Qxa1 (9... Qa3 10. Qxb7 $18) 10. Qxa1 $16) 9. Rxb1 c4 {Black
gains space and restricts the e2-bishop.} (9... b6 {looks dangerous for Black.
White can simply open the b-file and make use of it.} 10. dxc5 bxc5 11. Nb5 Kd8
12. Nd6 Bxd6 13. exd6 Nd7 14. Rb7 $14 {with an obvious advantage.}) 10. Rxb7
Nc6 11. Nb5 $1 {Strong move! The knight goes to d6 and at the same time
