{Taking the b2-pawn is premature. How can White punish his opponent?} 8. Qb1 $1
{This is an important move. When exchanging queens, White retains the
initiative and is ahead in development.} Qxb1+ (8... Qxc3+ $2 {You can not
take a Knight.} 9. Bd2 Qa3 10. Qxb7 $18) 9. Rxb1 c4 10. Rxb7 Nc6 11. Nb5 $1 Nd8
12. Rc7 Rb8 13. Nd6+ Bxd6 14. exd6 $16 {White is better developed and has
more active pieces. Additionally, the d6-pawn is very strong.} *

